# LucidGate example list: addheaderregexplist
# Format: Either "Header: value" for unconditional add, or "url-regex => Header: value" for conditional request header add.
# Lines beginning with # are comments and are ignored by the loader.
# To activate a rule, copy one example, remove the leading # and adapt it to your environment.
# You can include another file with: .Include<relative-or-absolute-path>
#
# Commented examples:
# X-LucidGate-Policy: default
# X-Content-Guard: enabled
# X-Proxy-Audit: sampled
# ^https://example\.test/secure => X-Secure-Zone: yes
# ^https://example\.test/api/ => X-API-Policy: restricted
# ^https://files\.example\.test/ => X-Download-Policy: strict
# ^https://portal\.example\.test/admin => X-Admin-Path: true
# X-Client-Inspection: on
# X-Policy-Version: 2026-06-01
# X-Org-Unit: example
